place.name: Puerto Sagua Restaurant
place.description: Puerto Sagua, a local Miami Beach Cuban restaurant is the hangout for old-world Cubans, politicos, club kids and just about everyone visiting beautiful South Beach. Since 1968 they've served an extensive menu of Cuban delicacies from Media Noches and Lechon with Moros to Yuca and more. For the ultimate Cuban dining experience in Miami Beach, visit Puerto Sagua today.

place.name: Avalon Hotel
place.description: If you want to stay right in the heart of South Beachs vibrant waterfront, there is no better place than Ocean Drives Avalon Hotel. Whether it is the colorful outdoor cafes, restaurants and hot nightclubs, the 30 upscale boutiques within 3 blocks or the sparkling white sands of South Beach that draws you, this tropical beachfront hotel is in the middle of it all

place.name: Mango's Tropical Cafe
place.description: Restaurant serving international cuisine transforms into nightclub with exotic drinks served by scantily clad bartenders dancing to live Latin music. Mangos is the best place to do it all in south beach. Everything is great from the drinks, dancers, food and bands. The place is full of energy and great music. You must go to Mango's!

place.name: Pelican Cafe
place.description: Pelican Café embodies the spirit of an authentic seaside restaurant; specializing in the art of seafood cuisine. A low profile side walk café welcomes you with impeccable service and attention to detail. As Miami Beach has changed with its wonderful eclectic residents so has the creativity of our executive chef. From the Peruvian coast our signature Ceviche and from the Italian peninsula the world renowned Frutti di Mare salad as well as the Queen of all dishes the marvelous Spanish Paella.

place.name: Art Deco Weekend
place.description: Art Deco Weekend is a wonderful celebration of all things Art Deco, sponsored by the Miami Design Preservation League.

place.name: Bass Museum of Art
place.description: The museum specializes in art from around the world from the Renaissance to modern art. The Bass Museum was founded in 1963 by the City of Miami Beach. The Museum creates and presents traveling exhibitions from national and international collections in order to stimulate tourism and provide an important cultural destination for Miami Beach.

place.name: World Erotic Art Museum
place.description: The WEAM private collection dates from antiquities to contemporary times and shows all cultures, art mediums and lifestyles in a tasteful historic time line. The collection includes paintings, tapestries, sculptures and art objects, mostly one of a kind.With over 20 rooms and 12,000 square feet, the WEAM has more than you can even imagine.

place.name: Uncle Sam's Music
place.description: Uncle Sam’s Music is located in the heart of South Miami Beach, Florida at the corner of Washington Avenue and 12th Street.

place.name: Mansion
place.description: One of South Beach’s most iconic venues, has set the stage for some of the music world’s most heralded events, parties and live performances. Featuring the most advanced lighting and sound in the US.

place.name: Set
place.description: SET features a luxurious mix of crystal, Pucci fabrics, baby croc and leather, a futuristic glass fireplace, vacuum-compressed elevators, eclectic Tinseltownera artifacts and ebony macassar, creating a vibe that gives a modern South Beach nod to old Hollywood glamour.

place.name: Myntlounge
place.description: Actors, models, rock stars, and other celebs frequent this futuristic-themed lounge, making one of the most exclusive around. If you manage to get it, you’ll find a small but hopping dance floor, cool music, modular white couches to lounge on, and a long bar serving very expensive drinks.

Mangos is the best place to do it all in south beach. Everything is great from the drinks, dancers, food and bands. The place is full of energy and great music. You must go to Mango's!

place.name: New World Symphony
place.description: The New World Symphony is the United States' only full-time orchestral academy preparing musicians for careers in symphony orchestras and ensembles. It was established in 1987 in Miami Beach, Florida, under the artistic direction of conductor Michael Tilson Thomas, in large part with a grant from Ted Arison, founder of Carnival Cruise Lines.

place.name: Uncle Sam's Music
place.description: Uncle Sam’s Music is located in the heart of South Miami Beach, Florida at the corner of Washington Avenue and 12th Street.

place.name: Van Dyke Cafe
place.description: Named as one of Time Magazine’s Miami: 10 Things to DO in 24 Hours in 2010. Van Dyke Café is a favorite for its international breakfast, lunch and dinner fares, and continues the tradition as the only venue on Lincoln Road to catch live musical performances nightly.

place.name: South Beach Chamber Ensemble, Inc.
place.description: The mission of the South Beach Chamber Ensemble is to promote and perform chamber music in all its diverse forms, from its origins in the distant past, to the varied cultural creations being produced today, bringing together performers, composers and audiences to experience the beauty and intimacy of the human spirit.
